{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Struffoli","content":["Place all dough ingredients except oil in mixing bowl then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>. Tip out onto a floured surface, and using your hands, roll pieces of dough into thin sticks (approx. 1 cm wide). Cut each stick into 0.5 cm pieces.","Heat oil in a large saucepan over a high heat.","Fry struffoli in hot oil, a few at a time, for about 5 minutes or until golden. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towel."]},{"title":"Icing","content":["Place honey, water, sugar, orange zest and lemon zest in mixing bowl then cook <b>8 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Pour liquid into a large saucepan and add struffoli and candied fruit then stir gently.","When liquid has been absorbed by struffoli, pour onto a round serving dish and, with your hands slightly wet, form a doughnut shape and allow to set before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Struffoli","content":["500 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","5 g butter","90 g sugar","50 g liqueur, Strega or Galliano","4 medium eggs","1 pinch ground cinnamon","1 pinch bicarbonate of soda","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 lemon, zest only, finely grated","1 orange, zest only, finely grated","1000 g groundnut oil for frying"]},{"title":"Icing","content":["300 g honey","25 g water","50 g sugar","1 orange, zest only, grated","1 lemon, zest only, grated","100 g candied orange peel"]}],"id":"r133238","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/--ky-gKNxMMk\/XZWddmBxKpI\/AAAAAAAAel4\/0F6vh6ymeiQrsSi6kvIZI12YEZ_5cWDfgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_H4kYicV19Z7xX3QP.png","title":"Struffoli (Italy)","publishedAt":"2016-12-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.4 g","fat":"14.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"43.8 g","calories":"1318 kJ \/ 315 kcal"},"usefulItems":"long sharp knife, large saucepan, slotted spoon, paper towel, serving dish, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Traditionally struffoli are decorated with coloured sprinkles (in Naples called 'diavulilli') and a sprinkling of cinnamon, lemon and candied pumpkin for fragrance. The latter is only found in Naples and is called 'cucuzzata.'","Strega and Galliano are Italian liqueurs flavoured with herbs.","If you have enough time, rest the dough before frying."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","1h 10m","20 portions"]}